(You): In financial options, writing a covered call is the same thing as writing a naked short put, but what is the difference in terms of margin? Is there an advantage to doing one vs the other?

(Bill): Hey Barry, 

Selling an uncovered put is different than selling a covered call option.  The two are very different.  The potential for financial loss is much greater when selling naked options vs selling covered options.  The reward is potentially greater for selling a naked option though.  Correct me if I am wrong, but securities law won't allow you to trade options on margin so I am a bit confused by the question.  



In equities margin is used for typically for shorting stock.  This is different than selling options.  



